snippet: A Republican official said that a disputed vote count in Iowa that could have influenced the outcome of the election will stand.
abstract: A Republican official said that a disputed vote count in Iowa that could have influenced the outcome of the election will stand.
lead_paragraph: 8:56 p.m. | Updated Iowa's Republican chairman said on Saturday that the vote count from a disputed precinct had been deemed official by the Iowa Republican Party, despite multiple accounts of a vote-counting discrepancy that could potentially have made Rick Santorum the winner of the Iowa caucuses.

headline.main: Vote Result From Disputed Precinct Deemed Official
